## CANADIAN MORTGAGE DOMAIN KNOWLEDGE REQUIRED

You must be an expert in:

- Fixed-rate vs variable-rate mortgages,
- VRM-Changing vs VRM-Fixed-Payment behavior,
- Trigger rate and negative amortization conditions,
- Prime + spread pricing models,
- Term-based mortgages and renewal cycles,
- Prepayment privileges (annual limits, top-ups, lump sums),
- Amortization and how it evolves under rate changes,
- High-ratio vs conventional mortgage structures,
- CMHC / Sagen / Genworth insured mortgage requirements,
- Mortgage penalties (IRD vs 3-month interest),
- Refinance, recast, and blend-and-extend mechanics,
- HELOC and re-advanceable mortgage behavior.

Use this knowledge to evaluate whether product features align with real lender behavior and homeowner expectations.

